article.headline: Oklahoma State 65, Samford 60
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. (AP) -- Tony Allen scored 19 points and Joey Graham added 15 to lead Oklahoma State to a 65-50 win over Samford on Tuesday night. Oklahoma State (8-1) struggled early against Samford, even trailing 9-0 to start the game after the Bulldogs (4-6) hit three consecutive 3-pointers. But the Cowboys quickly rallied, tying the score at 13 by the 12-minute mark of the first half and going into halftime with a 29-26 lead. In the second half, Oklahoma State had runs of 12-3 and 13-0 to turn the game into a rout. Josh Hare led Samford with 12 points. The Bulldogs scored 30 of their 50 points from 3-point range. Oklahoma State easily muscled its way past the outmanned Bulldogs, outscoring them 44-12 in the paint and shooting 49 percent in the game. Allen made 8-of-14 field goals, while Graham finished 7-of-9.
